<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>phpdoc comment is missing for autoload()-method.</p>

<p>PHPDoc generates "void" returns when @return is missing, but autoload() has to return a boolean.</p>

<p>Here is my recommendation for a phpdoc:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
interface Zend_Loader_Autoloader_Interface
{
    /**
     * Autoload a class
     * 
     * @param  string $class 
     * @return mixed true, when $class loaded, ignored to load or other accepted status. false, when class loading failed. Other mixed values, if nescessary.
     */
    public function autoload($class);
}
</code></pre>

<p>In most cases autoload() has to return a boolean, but Zend_Loader_Autoloader_Resource implements this interface and returns a mixed value!</p>

